{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"title":"JustText","modules":[{"name":"JustText"}],"externalID":"JustText","role":"collection","symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Command-line Tool"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A little library providing utility macros to use in C like languages.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a refined version of my older macro libraries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The naming tries to be consistent, by that I mean I just use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"JT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" prefix everywhere.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"I don’t bother with internal prefixes, because library is too small for that.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This library uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":" which is not standard C (not yet, I think)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"text":" is provided either by the GNU C extension or by the C++ 20 Standard.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"So if you don’t have any of those,  then ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"text":" is probably not working.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"And that means the most important macroses of this library will not work for you correctly."}]}],"style":"warning","name":"Warning","type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"So, gotta have "},{"code":"__VA_OPT__","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without it it’s very hard to implement recursion in macros, at least that’s what I concluded. That the most readable version","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ForEach"},{"type":"text","text":" macros and such can be achived only with this "},{"code":"__VA_OPT__","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stuff; I think it can be simulated more or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"less with standard stuff, but not worth the effor I think."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Perhaps there are other things I used here, which are not standard, but I have no idea of them","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Internal-and-Public-Macros","text":"Internal and Public Macros"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The separation on public and internal macroses are not very strict, meaning you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use internal macroses as well as public ones. I just suppose public macros are gonna","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be much more useful in practice, then the internal ones.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"But I provide documentation for some of them anyway, because they are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"important to understand how this library works."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/Debugging","doc:\/\/JustText\/tutorials\/WhyMacros"]},{"text":"Things to be done","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Things-to-be-done"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Divide into sub files"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Write zipWith variadic macro for 2 variadic lists —> Done, but make work for different sizes"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Write genericTranspose macro for variadic amount of variadic lists ??"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"}]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After all, it’s just a bunch of text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Public-Commons","title":"Public Commons","identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTIf","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTString","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTCount"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTForEach","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMap","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMapPlain","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMapComma","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMapParenSep","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMapMakeSep"],"anchor":"Public-Mappers","title":"Public Mappers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTZip","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTZipPlain","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTZipComma"],"title":"Public Zippers","anchor":"Public-Zippers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTApp","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTGetThird","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTParens","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTGetStringForReal","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTOne","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTExpand","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTMassExpand","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTPseudoNewLine"],"title":"Basic internals","anchor":"Basic-internals"},{"anchor":"Internal-Separator-Extractors","title":"Internal Separator Extractors","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"### Internal Map Support"}],"identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTParensSepExtractor","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTSepProducerExtractor","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTPlainSepE